                  </hi>. I had offices at 46, Moorgate Street, but I have removed to 49, Cornhill—I did not take 100 shares in this company in January, 1875—Pryor told me he had taken shares in my name, that he, had paid for them, and that I was his nominee—I never paid any money for them, nor received any dividends upon them—I believe Pryor handed me this cheque to sign—I endorsed and handed it to him Again, but know no more about it.</p>
