                  </hi>. I come from the National Provincial Bank, St. James's—Mr. Barnard had an account there of 167<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. from 24th January—he was not entitled to overdraw, and a cheque being presented for 250<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. would be referred to the manager—his account was closed on 15th June—he had 200<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. once to his credit, but not for a whole day—250<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. was never to his credit.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18780624-name-72" type="witnessName">
